main event: Seven bright, round, fast-moving light objects were observed maneuvering in the sky over Rapid City, South Dakota from 1:00 AM to 2:30 AM on July 21, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were described as flying at an altitude of about 10,000 feet and covering distances of about 30-40 miles in 10-15 seconds, changing speed and direction abruptly.
No other aircraft were observed in the area at the time.
The report states that no conclusions have been reached as to the identity of the objects.
The report is signed by Floyd B. McMorrow, Special Investigator, OSI, 4602nd Air Intelligence Service Squadron.
sighted object: seven bright, round, fast-moving light objects
